Jeff,

This is also possible in brms and in Stan directly. There is vignette that describes how to do it: https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/brms/vignettes/brms_distreg.html. You can fit relatively simple unequal variance models with "fixed effects" or complex smooth terms (via splines). The learning curve might be steep if you're not familiar with Bayesian models. Richard McElreath's Statistical Rethinking and lectures are a good introduction, and has lots of ecology content. 
 
Jason


